## Assistant (Compaction · Big Pickle · 18.1s)

_Thinking:_

Let me create a comprehensive summary of the entire conversation, based on all the exchanges and the actual state of the project.

## Objective
- Build a Facebook Ads Library Lead Extractor that runs locally on the user's Windows machine using Node.js, extracting business leads (names, website URLs, phone numbers, WhatsApp links) from Facebook Ads Library URLs and outputting them to Excel.

## Important Details
- User runs `npm start` in `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper` to launch the server on `http://localhost:3000`
- Excel export must be .xlsx compatible with Excel 2019 (ExcelJS library used)
- FB_HEADLESS is `true` by default in `.env`; if login is needed, user must change to `false`, log in via the visible Chrome window, then switch back
- Facebook scraper now uses text parsing (splitting page text by "See ad details") instead of fragile DOM selectors like `[role="article"]`
- Phone numbers must include context labels (e.g., "Wac: +252614724520") so they aren't confused when multiple numbers appear in one cell
- WhatsApp regex updated to handle spaces in numbers (e.g., `https://wa.me/25261 3992132`)
- No persistent cookie storage between runs; Playwright launches fresh each time

## Work State
### Completed
- Installed dependencies: express, playwright, cheerio, axios, libphonenumber-js, ws, dotenv, exceljs
- Created full project structure: server.js, src/ (config, routes, controllers, services, utils), public/ (index.html, css, js)
- Rewrote Facebook scraper (facebookAdsScraper.js) to use text-based parsing: scrolls page, splits on "See ad details", extracts business name, phones, WhatsApp, website URLs, CTAs
- Fixed WhatsApp link regex to capture numbers with spaces (`[\d\s\-\.\+]+` instead of `\d+`)
- Website scraper (websiteScraper.js) crawls homepage, /contact, /about, internal contact pages for phone numbers
- Scraper service (scraperService.js) merges Facebook-extracted phones with website-crawled phones, deduplicating
- Configured .env with sensible defaults (FB_HEADLESS=true, FB_SCROLL_DELAY=2000, CRAWL_TIMEOUT=20000)
- Export service (exportService.js) generates .xlsx with ExcelJS (bold header row, blue fill, auto-width, phone columns formatted as text)
- Frontend dashboard (Bootstrap 5 dark mode): progress bar, stats cards, searchable/paginated table, export button, session history
- Backend server with WebSocket for real-time progress updates
- Phone number extraction confirmed working for Somali numbers and WhatsApp links
- Created debug script (temp/debug_dom.js) to inspect Facebook DOM structure

### Active
- Modifying phoneExtractor.js to return labeled phone objects `{ label, number }` instead of raw strings, so each number carries its context (e.g., "Wac", "Tel", "WhatsApp")
- Updating websiteScraper.js, scraperService.js, exportService.js, and frontend to handle labeled phone format
- Improving dedup logic to treat `0614724520` and `252614724520` as the same number

### Blocked
- (none)

## Next Move
1. Complete phoneExtractor.js rewrite to return labeled phone objects with context labels from surrounding text
2. Update websiteScraper.js to use the new labeled phone format
3. Update scraperService.js merge logic for labeled phones
4. Update exportService.js to display labeled phones in Excel
5. Update frontend (app.js) to display labels in the table
6. Test end-to-end from URL paste to Excel download

## Relevant Files
- `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper\src\utils\phoneExtractor.js`: core phone & WhatsApp extraction, being rewritten to return labeled objects
- `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper\src\services\facebookAdsScraper.js`: Facebook Ads Library text-based scraper (working)
- `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper\src\services\websiteScraper.js`: website crawler for phone numbers
- `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper\src\services\scraperService.js`: orchestrator merging Facebook + website data
- `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper\src\services\exportService.js`: Excel .xlsx generator using ExcelJS
- `C:\Users\SomaliRank\Desktop\dubia store\facebook scapper\public\js\app.js`: frontend dashboard logic
